commit.message:
re PR testsuite/41146 (FAIL: gcc.target/powerpc/asm-es-2.c scan-assembler *)

2011-01-18  Dominique d'Humieres  <dominiq@lps.ens.fr>

	PR testsuite/41146
	* gcc.target/powerpc/asm-es-2.c: Adjust regular expression for
	powerpc-apple-darwin9.

From-SVN: r168960

files.patch:
@@ -1,3 +1,9 @@
+2011-01-18  Dominique d'Humieres  <dominiq@lps.ens.fr>
+
+	PR testsuite/41146
+	* gcc.target/powerpc/asm-es-2.c: Adjust regular expression for
+	powerpc-apple-darwin9.
+
 2011-01-18  Jakub Jelinek  <jakub@redhat.com>
 
 	PR rtl-optimization/47299
@@ -75,7 +81,7 @@
 
 2011-01-13  Jan Hubicka  <jh@suse.cz>
 
-	PR tree-optimization/47276 
+	PR tree-optimization/47276
 	* gcc.dg/pr47276.c: New testcase.
 
 2011-01-15  Giovanni Funchal  <gafunchal@gmail.com>
@@ -201,7 +207,7 @@
 	* objc-obj-c++-shared/Object1-implementation.h: Add copyright header.
 	Amend implementation to use a TEST_SUITE_ADDITIONS category for both GNU
 	and NeXT runtimes.
-	* objc-obj-c++-shared/Object1.mm: Remove redundant header, update 
+	* objc-obj-c++-shared/Object1.mm: Remove redundant header, update
 	comments.
 	* objc-obj-c++-shared/Object1.m: Likewise.
 	* objc.dg/encode-3.m: Update header use.  Amend to be API2 compatible.

@@ -31,7 +31,7 @@ f4 (int *p)
   asm ("asm4 %0" : "=es" (p[100]));
 }
 
-/* { dg-final { scan-assembler "asm1 3,4" } } */
-/* { dg-final { scan-assembler "asm2u 16\\(3\\)" } } */
-/* { dg-final { scan-assembler "asm3 0\\(3\\)" } } */
-/* { dg-final { scan-assembler "asm4 400\\(3\\)" } } */
+/* { dg-final { scan-assembler "asm1 %?r?3,%?r?4" } } */
+/* { dg-final { scan-assembler "asm2u 16\\(%?r?3\\)" } } */
+/* { dg-final { scan-assembler "asm3 0\\(%?r?3\\)" } } */
+/* { dg-final { scan-assembler "asm4 400\\(%?r?3\\)" } } */
